  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q3" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: Almost 1 in 2 children have one.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p class="hangingIndent1">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q4" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: It is clear that a large proportion of all children, just over 50 per cent, have some kind of equipment in their bedroom and that the percentage is considerably higher for boys.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q5" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: The television is closely followed by games consoles in popularity.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q6" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: The only exception is video cassette recorders, which are slightly more common in girls' bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q7" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: A third of boys own such consoles compared to only a fifth of girls.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q8" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: A closer look at the figures shows that the most common appliance found in children's bedrooms is the television set.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <input id="q9" type="droptarget"/>
      <font color="#000000">: However, these are far more popular with boys than with girls.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff"><input id="q10" type="droptarget"/>: The bar chart shows the percentages of girls and boys with home entertainment equipment in their bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"/></font>
